3
00:00:15,160 --> 00:00:17,120
Oh, crap!

4
00:00:20,250 --> 00:00:21,170
Who's there?

5
00:00:26,800 --> 00:00:28,760
Th-They killed him!

6
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:31,340
They actually offed Cobra!

7
00:00:31,340 --> 00:00:35,680
I may not have liked the guy,
but I haven't sunk so low I'd celebrate!

8
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:38,850
I saw something I shouldn't have!

9
00:00:48,280 --> 00:00:51,490
I just had a brush with the dark side
of the World Government!

10
00:00:51,490 --> 00:00:53,280
I never asked for this!

11
00:00:53,280 --> 00:00:54,910
What was that thing?!

12
00:00:54,910 --> 00:00:57,160
My life is completely over!

13
00:01:04,130 --> 00:01:08,130
King Cobra and King Wapol
have yet to arrive...

14
00:01:08,510 --> 00:01:10,590
We just received a message.

15
00:01:10,590 --> 00:01:13,300
They both requested
that you carry on without them.

16
00:01:13,300 --> 00:01:17,060
I guess King Cobra used up all his energy
on that impassioned speech!

17
00:01:19,270 --> 00:01:22,730
He must be satisfied with how
the matter of the Warlords was settled.

18
00:01:23,440 --> 00:01:24,400
Now then!

19
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:26,860
Let's finish up the rest of our agenda.

20
00:01:26,860 --> 00:01:30,190
First, the independence of
the North Blue's Four-Nation Alliance...

21
00:01:31,070 --> 00:01:32,570
♪ Akamambo! ♪

22
00:01:32,570 --> 00:01:34,160
♪ Shake, shake! ♪

23
00:01:34,160 --> 00:01:35,740
Shirahoshi.

24
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:37,870
The council will soon adjourn.

25
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:40,330
Let's wait at the Red Port without these fools.

26
00:01:40,330 --> 00:01:41,460
Of course.

27
00:01:44,170 --> 00:01:44,960
What's wrong?

28
00:01:45,460 --> 00:01:49,340
I wanted to bid farewell to Princess Vivi.

29
00:01:49,960 --> 00:01:52,430
Wherever could she have gone?

30
00:01:58,140 --> 00:02:00,100
Why are you doing this?!

31
00:02:00,100 --> 00:02:01,560
Untie these ropes!

32
00:02:01,560 --> 00:02:03,020
Who ordered this?

33
00:02:03,020 --> 00:02:06,400
I'll tell the whole world what happened here!

34
00:02:08,110 --> 00:02:10,780
Whoa there, nobody likes a rat.

35
00:02:10,780 --> 00:02:13,860
What kind of idiot would
set you free after hearing that?

36
00:02:13,860 --> 00:02:15,570
You are one feisty lady!

37
00:02:18,870 --> 00:02:20,290
I hate to say it...

38
00:02:20,290 --> 00:02:23,290
but no one's coming to save you, Princess.

39
00:02:23,290 --> 00:02:27,540
You'll probably just be reported as "missing"
and wind up as someone's pet.

40
00:02:28,750 --> 00:02:30,210
Is Shirahoshi okay?

41
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:33,550
Seriously? Shouldn't you be worrying
about yourself right now?

42
00:02:37,010 --> 00:02:41,720
It sounds like there was another incident
earlier, but long story short, she's fine.

43
00:02:42,140 --> 00:02:43,430
Thank goodness...

44
00:02:43,430 --> 00:02:48,270
The guys who beat up the Celestial Dragon
trying to kidnap the mermaid...

45
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:52,490
– We're Straw Hat Luffy's subordinates!
– We're Straw Hat Luffy's subordinates!

46
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:59,660
...proudly declared themselves the winners
and sent the plaza into a frenzy.

47
00:03:02,120 --> 00:03:04,460
On top of that, in the Land of the Gods...

48
00:03:05,370 --> 00:03:09,210
Fujitora helped the Revolutionaries
free the slaves,

49
00:03:09,210 --> 00:03:11,960
which pissed off Ryokugyu,
and they got in a big fight...

50
00:03:12,460 --> 00:03:14,170
Sheesh...

51
00:03:14,170 --> 00:03:16,880
This year's Reverie has been one big mess.

52
00:03:18,090 --> 00:03:21,470
I have to do something... Be someone's pet?

53
00:03:22,010 --> 00:03:23,310
What a sick joke!

54
00:03:29,400 --> 00:03:30,400
Someone's...!

55
00:03:36,150 --> 00:03:38,110
Help me!

56
00:03:38,110 --> 00:03:40,780
I didn't see nothin'!

57
00:03:40,780 --> 00:03:41,780
Wapol?!

58
00:03:41,780 --> 00:03:43,620
Outta my way!

59
00:03:43,620 --> 00:03:44,450
That's it!

60
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,380
Clear the way!

61
00:03:51,210 --> 00:03:52,550
I ain't...

62
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:55,510
getting caught!

63
00:04:00,300 --> 00:04:02,720
What was that about?

64
00:04:02,720 --> 00:04:04,680
That was King Wapol, right?

65
00:04:06,930 --> 00:04:08,140
Hey, wait!

66
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:09,600
Vivi's gone!

67
00:04:09,600 --> 00:04:11,360
What?!

68
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,700
Hey!

69
00:04:18,910 --> 00:04:20,870
Salutations, Queen Kinderella.

70
00:04:20,870 --> 00:04:22,490
Have you seen my husband?

71
00:04:22,490 --> 00:04:24,990
No, I'm afraid I haven't.

72
00:04:31,500 --> 00:04:33,340
Oh, my!

73
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:33,340
King Wapol!

74
00:04:33,340 --> 00:04:35,800
I've been looking for you, darling!

75
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,800
Where have you been?!

76
00:04:43,260 --> 00:04:45,430
Who is that young woman?!

77
00:04:46,020 --> 00:04:48,180
Hey, Wapol! How far are you gonna go?!

78
00:04:48,180 --> 00:04:49,440
As far as I freakin' can!

79
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:52,150
To the ends of the world
where no one will catch me!

80
00:04:52,650 --> 00:04:54,320
Well, count me in!

81
00:04:54,320 --> 00:04:55,230
Take me with you!

82
00:04:57,190 --> 00:05:02,620
Are they eloping?!

83
00:06:33,210 --> 00:06:37,540
With the truth of King Cobra's
murder kept under wraps,

84
00:06:37,540 --> 00:06:40,590
the curtain came down on the Reverie.

85
00:06:41,210 --> 00:06:42,630
Let me see King Cobra!

86
00:06:43,090 --> 00:06:45,340
We were ordered to bar all entry.

87
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:46,340
Depart at once!

88
00:06:46,340 --> 00:06:48,550
What's going on in there?!

89
00:06:48,550 --> 00:06:51,020
His Highness is very ill!

90
00:06:54,390 --> 00:06:56,230
King Cobra!

91
00:06:56,230 --> 00:06:57,940
Attention, everyone!

92
00:06:57,940 --> 00:07:02,440
Has anyone seen Princess Vivi
of the Kingdom of Alabasta?!

93
00:07:02,440 --> 00:07:04,280
This is Princess Vivi!

94
00:07:04,280 --> 00:07:05,280
Have you seen her?!

95
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:09,830
Where could you be?

96
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,330
Princess Vivi!

97
00:07:18,460 --> 00:07:19,710
Let's hurry up!

98
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,590
That's a royal family's cargo.

99
00:07:21,590 --> 00:07:23,130
Treat it with care.

100
00:07:23,130 --> 00:07:24,050
– Got it!
– Got it!

101
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:36,270
King Tea IV is on board now!

102
00:07:36,690 --> 00:07:38,770
Hurry up with that luggage!

103
00:07:38,770 --> 00:07:40,110
– On it!
– On it!

104
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,200
We managed to sneak on somehow.

105
00:07:52,200 --> 00:07:54,040
It's safe for now...

106
00:07:54,540 --> 00:07:56,790
But now what do I do?

107
00:07:56,790 --> 00:07:59,170
I can't keep quiet about the Reverie!

108
00:07:59,170 --> 00:08:01,540
I'm doomed!

109
00:08:01,540 --> 00:08:04,670
Why do these things keep happening to me?!

110
00:08:04,670 --> 00:08:05,920
Hey!

111
00:08:05,920 --> 00:08:07,220
Keep it down!

112
00:08:07,220 --> 00:08:08,840
Oh, yeah!

113
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:12,050
I bet he won't let me down.

114
00:08:12,050 --> 00:08:15,770
I've got just the kinda scoop
for a guy like him...

115
00:08:15,770 --> 00:08:17,350
A transponder snail?!

116
00:08:22,270 --> 00:08:24,980
Morrie, baby! It's me, Wapol!

117
00:08:24,980 --> 00:08:27,860
Oh, it's been a while!

118
00:08:27,860 --> 00:08:29,700
How was the Reverie?

119
00:08:29,700 --> 00:08:32,280
I can't talk about it over the snail!

120
00:08:32,660 --> 00:08:34,660
They'll kill me if they find out!

121
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:38,620
So in exchange for my story,
I want you to grant me asylum!

122
00:08:39,540 --> 00:08:41,170
Sure thing.

123
00:08:41,170 --> 00:08:43,040
Where are you now?

124
00:08:43,040 --> 00:08:46,300
Hey! What country's ship is this?

125
00:08:46,300 --> 00:08:47,760
The Kingdom of Eigis.

126
00:08:48,130 --> 00:08:51,970
Got it. We'll swing by and act like
we're doing research for an article.

127
00:08:51,970 --> 00:08:54,100
Use that chance to get on our ship.

128
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,470
Don't let anyone see you.

129
00:08:55,470 --> 00:08:56,680
I owe you one!

130
00:08:59,730 --> 00:09:01,940
Now that's what I'm talkin' about!

131
00:09:02,310 --> 00:09:06,650
A story so big it threatens a king's life!

132
00:09:07,280 --> 00:09:09,610
This is gonna be good!

133
00:09:10,860 --> 00:09:14,410
So what exactly did you see, Wapol?

134
00:09:14,410 --> 00:09:15,950
Not out loud!

135
00:09:15,950 --> 00:09:19,120
You're the last person I want to tell about it!

136
00:09:19,120 --> 00:09:22,080
Why don't you go back to your people?!

137
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,330
Absolutely not.

138
00:09:23,330 --> 00:09:25,960
Those were CP0 agents.

139
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:30,090
Even if I return to my people,
I'll just be abducted again.

140
00:09:30,470 --> 00:09:32,720
So let me use your transponder snail!

141
00:09:33,550 --> 00:09:36,680
I have to call my father.

142
00:09:36,680 --> 00:09:38,020
He's such a worrywart.

143
00:09:38,020 --> 00:09:40,770
No! You absolutely cannot!

144
00:09:40,770 --> 00:09:42,480
That's the last thing you should do!

145
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:43,730
Why not?!

146
00:09:43,730 --> 00:09:45,560
Just let me use it for a bit!

147
00:10:00,410 --> 00:10:02,120
I'm starving...

148
00:10:10,090 --> 00:10:13,930
If I can just make it to Lulusia,
I can figure something out...

149
00:10:13,970 --> 00:10:17,430
I'm counting on you, Sabo!

150
00:10:17,470 --> 00:10:19,520
You must live on!

151
00:10:23,230 --> 00:10:29,570
Vivi, Wapol, and a few other stowaways
held their breaths anxiously,

152
00:10:29,570 --> 00:10:32,900
hiding on the ships carrying monarchs
back to their homes.

153
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:39,160
Before long, news of King Cobra's murder and the disappearance of Princess Vivi,

154
00:10:39,160 --> 00:10:44,460
both of the Kingdom of Alabasta,
spread throughout the world.

155
00:10:44,460 --> 00:10:50,170
Sabo is yet another man
burdened with a strange fate.

156
00:10:50,170 --> 00:10:54,680
No one has led a life more affected by the D.

157
00:10:54,680 --> 00:10:59,640
It's time to put this Egghead business to rest.

158
00:11:03,270 --> 00:11:04,850
Yes, Esteemed Imu.

159
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:11,280
I would like to use this "Mother Flame"
Vegapunk has invented.

160
00:11:11,650 --> 00:11:17,490
Indeed, we cannot be sure if it
is real until it has been tested.

161
00:11:17,490 --> 00:11:22,950
Let us decide on a course of action for Egghead
based on the results of this experiment.

162
00:11:22,950 --> 00:11:27,040
A test on forested land
would be preferable to one at sea...

163
00:11:27,040 --> 00:11:29,250
The Kingdom of Lulusia.

164
00:11:30,420 --> 00:11:32,550
Quite a lot of people live there.

165
00:11:32,550 --> 00:11:34,010
It matters not.

166
00:11:34,010 --> 00:11:35,880
Understood.

167
00:11:35,880 --> 00:11:38,970
The world should be as the creators desire.

168
00:11:38,970 --> 00:11:41,810
Why did you choose Lulusia?

169
00:11:44,350 --> 00:11:45,980
It is close.

170
00:11:45,980 --> 00:11:47,100
Indeed.

171
00:11:56,780 --> 00:12:01,240
We shall make the necessary preparations.
We humbly request your patience.

172
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:05,450
There are signs of revolt
among the Lulusian people.

173
00:12:05,830 --> 00:12:08,670
This will serve as an example to everyone.

174
00:12:09,040 --> 00:12:13,000
Eventually, when we have
that power at our disposal...

175
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:16,590
...this ancient battle will come to an end.

176
00:12:18,510 --> 00:12:20,760
One more thing.

177
00:12:20,760 --> 00:12:21,600
Yes.

178
00:12:22,810 --> 00:12:25,060
I want Vivi.

179
00:12:25,060 --> 00:12:26,520
– As you wish.
– As you wish.

180
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:50,750
Report for Fleet Admiral Sakazuki!

181
00:12:51,130 --> 00:12:53,960
The Kingdoms of Tajine and Eigis are revolting!

182
00:12:53,960 --> 00:12:57,920
Just crush every last one of them!

183
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:00,090
Hurry up! Get a move on!

184
00:13:04,760 --> 00:13:07,470
Deploy every seraphim!

185
00:13:07,850 --> 00:13:10,940
Crocodile has appeared on Empty Bluffs Island!

186
00:13:11,560 --> 00:13:14,610
The Marines found themselves stretched thin...

187
00:13:15,190 --> 00:13:19,030
between the end of the Warlords
and quelling unrest in member countries.

188
00:13:19,610 --> 00:13:24,740
However, this was merely the Marines
kickstarting their new approach.

189
00:13:27,290 --> 00:13:29,750
As soon as we arrived
at the Kingdom of Lulusia,

190
00:13:29,750 --> 00:13:32,250
King Seki and Princess Comane
were taken prisoner

191
00:13:32,620 --> 00:13:36,170
by their own citizens,
who had been waiting for them.

192
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:39,920
Just shut up and let me out of here!

193
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:50,560
Despite being a stowaway,
they welcomed me with open arms.

194
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:55,900
Vell, that is vhaat you get for being
a shining beacon of hope.

195
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:59,230
That's when I first saw the newspaper article...

196
00:13:59,940 --> 00:14:03,700
and learned that I had been
framed for regicide.

197
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:08,990
Unsurprisingly, the people
quickly hailed me as a hero.

198
00:14:09,620 --> 00:14:13,330
I wanted to tell the truth,
but I held my tongue.

199
00:14:14,250 --> 00:14:16,790
The flames of revolution
were burning inside them.

200
00:14:19,380 --> 00:14:21,260
Thanks to Betty and the others,

201
00:14:21,260 --> 00:14:25,430
many Lulusians were interested
in joining the Revolutionary Army.

202
00:14:25,430 --> 00:14:28,390
They're the ones that I brought here.

203
00:14:30,970 --> 00:14:35,190
In the end, I couldn't procure an encryption
transponder snail in Lulusia,

204
00:14:35,560 --> 00:14:37,900
so I wasn't able to call you.

205
00:14:37,900 --> 00:14:44,990
The call I did make was a relay call
as soon as we left port.

206
00:14:45,570 --> 00:14:47,030
Dragon!

207
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:48,950
King Cobra's assassin...

208
00:14:51,620 --> 00:14:53,080
wasn't me!

209
00:14:55,210 --> 00:15:01,670
The government must have picked up on
that signal and assumed I was in Lulusia.

210
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:05,260
But in reality, I was already
at sea with our new enlistees.

211
00:15:05,630 --> 00:15:09,010
It happened during your call, no?

212
00:15:09,010 --> 00:15:12,220
Vhenn the Kingdom of Lulusia vass eradicated?

213
00:15:12,220 --> 00:15:13,520
Yes...

214
00:15:14,440 --> 00:15:17,150
Panic swept through the ship.

215
00:15:17,650 --> 00:15:20,610
Many of them had left their families behind.

216
00:15:20,980 --> 00:15:24,700
They watched the destruction of
their home right in front of them!

217
00:15:26,660 --> 00:15:28,870
That must have been harrowing.

218
00:15:29,410 --> 00:15:31,370
What happened exactly?

219
00:15:33,830 --> 00:15:38,170
A great shadow blacked out the sky...

220
00:15:38,420 --> 00:15:41,960
and just like that, the island was...

221
00:15:53,470 --> 00:15:55,430
A great shadow?

222
00:15:55,430 --> 00:15:59,190
There's no way it was something biological,
or even a natural occurrence.

223
00:15:59,190 --> 00:16:02,190
There was some dark thing
flying above the clouds.

224
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,030
By the vayy, Sabo...

225
00:16:09,030 --> 00:16:12,030
you mentioned an "Imu" earlier, yes?

226
00:16:12,030 --> 00:16:13,330
Yeah.

227
00:16:13,330 --> 00:16:15,750
This is going to sound absolutely outrageous,

228
00:16:16,120 --> 00:16:21,460
but among the First Tvennty
who created this voorld 800 years ago,

229
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:24,880
there vass a ruler named
Saint Imu from the Nerona dynasty.

230
00:16:24,880 --> 00:16:25,920
What?!

231
00:16:26,550 --> 00:16:28,090
Take a look at this.

232
00:16:29,010 --> 00:16:33,470
Vee know there exists an ability
that can impart immortality,

233
00:16:33,470 --> 00:16:36,680
vhiich means somevonne must have
used it successfully, no?

234
00:16:36,680 --> 00:16:41,310
This means that somevonne
out there has never known death!

235
00:16:42,150 --> 00:16:44,400
Then... you're saying...

236
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,610
that's the person I saw?!

237
00:16:46,610 --> 00:16:49,570
That they share a name
might just be a coincidence...

238
00:16:49,950 --> 00:16:53,200
but if the Five Elders are the highest authority

239
00:16:53,200 --> 00:16:57,250
among the Celestial Dragons, who
fancy themselves descendants of the gods...

240
00:16:57,250 --> 00:16:59,960
then who else could make them fall in line?!

241
00:17:02,290 --> 00:17:05,000
And there is vonne more shocking thing!

242
00:17:05,420 --> 00:17:11,680
If that thing you saw over the clouds
destroying Lulusia vass a government veaapon...

243
00:17:12,010 --> 00:17:15,640
only Vegapunk could have
engineered such a thing!

244
00:17:15,640 --> 00:17:17,020
Wait, Iva.

245
00:17:17,020 --> 00:17:21,980
Vegapunk would never create a tool
so clearly designed for murder.

246
00:17:21,980 --> 00:17:23,560
Right?!

247
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:28,360
So... vhaat if it vass an ancient veaapon?

248
00:17:28,780 --> 00:17:33,070
It all makes sense if Imu is someone
who has been around since ancient times.

249
00:17:34,530 --> 00:17:39,120
Robin confirmed the existence
of the ancient weapons.

250
00:17:40,580 --> 00:17:44,330
But if they were in possession of such a thing,

251
00:17:44,330 --> 00:17:47,050
why haven't they used it before?

252
00:17:47,050 --> 00:17:49,760
And why would they use it now?

253
00:17:56,010 --> 00:17:57,470
In the present day,

254
00:17:57,470 --> 00:18:02,640
a Celestial Dragon has just been executed
in the Holy Land, Mary Geoise.

255
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:06,650
However, the public will never hear of his death.

256
00:18:06,650 --> 00:18:08,650
Good riddance.

257
00:18:08,650 --> 00:18:10,740
Because he took their side,

258
00:18:10,740 --> 00:18:14,950
these Lower Realm peasants
have been pushing their luck lately!

259
00:18:14,950 --> 00:18:18,910
It's all his fault that we lost
our food supply!

260
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:24,920
The judge was a man who was once hailed
as a champion on an island called God Valley.

261
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:29,210
He is now the supreme commander
of the Holy Knights.

262
00:18:29,210 --> 00:18:32,380
His name is St. Figarland Garling.

263
00:18:35,180 --> 00:18:36,800
The one executed...

264
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,260
was the man who defended the fishmen.

265
00:18:39,810 --> 00:18:42,980
St. Donquixote Mjosgard.

266
00:18:43,350 --> 00:18:47,400
Those who defend scum
are lower than the scum they protect.

